An Act
ENROLLED SENATE
BILL NO. 2110 By: Murdock and Nice of the
Senate
and
Worthen and Newton of the
House
An Act relating to agriculture; amending 2 O.S. 2021,
Section 10-78, which relates to the sale of eggs;
allowing for sale of certain eggs in specified
locations; establishing limit on sale of ungraded
eggs; and providing an effective date.
SUBJECT: Sale of eggs
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 10-78, is
amended to read as follows:
Section 10-78. A. Oklahoma producers of eggs selling ungraded
eggs from their own flock production are exempt from this
subarticle. Nothing in this subarticle shall prohibit the sale of
eggs produced on the farm and sold direct to the consumer on the
farm, at a farmers’ market, or otherwise off the farm direct to the
consumer. Eggs sold under this section shall be produced by hens
maintained on the farm from which the eggs are sold.
B. To be eligible to sell ungraded eggs pursuant to the
provisions of subsection A of this section, an egg producer in this
state shall be limited to the sale of no more than one hundred fifty
(150) dozen eggs per month.

C. A producer may sell graded eggs if in compliance with this
subarticle.
SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
